Heat oven to 400 degrees F. Spray 13x9 inch glass baking dish with nonstick cooking spray. Place Simply Potatoes(R) and sour cream in baking dish; stir together. Spread Simply Potatoes(R) evenly over bottom of baking dish. Rub both sides of each chicken thigh with mesquite seasoning. Place on top of potatoes. Cover; bake 40 to 45 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Uncover; top chicken with salsa verde. Sprinkle with cheese. Continue baking, uncovered, 5 minutes or until cheese is melted. Serve chicken and potatoes with avocado and green onions.